&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Crate / Repo:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://github.com/oxibus/automotive_diag" rel="external noopener" target="_blank"&gt;https://github.com/oxibus/automotive_diag&lt;svg class="link__external-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="M8.75 3a.75.75 0 0 0 0 1.5h2.69L6.22 9.72a.75.75 0 1 0 1.06 1.06l5.22-5.22v2.69a.75.75 0 0 0 1.5 0V3.75A.75.75 0 0 0 13.25 3H8.75Z"/&gt;&lt;path d="M2 4.75A2.75 2.75 0 0 1 4.75 2h2a.75.75 0 0 1 0 1.5h-2A1.25 1.25 0 0 0 3.5 4.75v6.5c0 .69.56 1.25 1.25 1.25h6.5c.69 0 1.25-.56 1.25-1.25v-2a.75.75 0 0 1 1.5 0v2A2.75 2.75 0 0 1 11.25 14h-6.5A2.75 2.75 0 0 1 2 11.25v-6.5Z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>UDS Architecture</title><link>https://avant-tecno-oy-uds-library.pages.avant-tecno-oy.ghe.com/docs/v0.0.1/en/planning/uds_architecture/</link><pubDate>Mon, 18 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://avant-tecno-oy-uds-library.pages.avant-tecno-oy.ghe.com/docs/v0.0.1/en/planning/uds_architecture/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="overview" class="heading"&gt;Overview&lt;a href="#overview" class="heading__anchor" aria-label="Link to this section" tabindex="-1"&gt;
 &lt;svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;
 &lt;path d="M7.775 3.275a.75.75 0 0 0 1.06 1.06l1.25-1.25a2 2 0 1 1 2.83 2.83l-2.5 2.5a2 2 0 0 1-2.83 0 .75.75 0 0 0-1.06 1.06 3.5 3.5 0 0 0 4.95 0l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 0-4.95-4.95l-1.25 1.25zm-4.69 9.64a2 2 0 0 1 0-2.83l2.5-2.5a2 2 0 0 1 2.83 0 .75.75 0 0 0 1.06-1.06 3.5 3.5 0 0 0-4.95 0l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 4.95 4.95l1.25-1.25a.75.75 0 0 0-1.06-1.06l-1.25 1.25a2 2 0 0 1-2.83 0z"/&gt;
 &lt;/svg&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The library is a mostly client-side (tester)(To be further refined on the role during meetings) UDS implementation written in Rust. It targets embedded Linux as the primary platform, with Windows as a secondary target. The design uses a layered architecture so that backends (CAN, DoIP) can be swapped without touching the UDS service layer.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>